Hundreds of protesters have set up camp outside Zuccotti Square.
Some protesters heard the court ruling to disband the demonstration from the square and headed to the park next door.
The Occupy Wall Street movement challenged New York City authorities on Tuesday when they tried to re-enter, under the protection of a court order, Manhattan Square, from where they were evacuated at dawn in an attempt to seize another Big Apple park.
Hundreds of protesters gathered outside Zuccotti Square, where they wanted to go thanks to a court order that allowed "angry people" to camp in the square while another part of the movement responded by seizing a park in the north of the city where further arrests were made.
