Bray explained that the response of "angry people" to the tent city evacuation order, which was personally given by New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg, went to court, where Judge Lucy Billings issued a ruling prohibiting forced evacuation from the square and allowing the protesters to remain in the camp.
In addition, the "angry men" have begun seizing a new park at the intersection of Canal Street and Sixth Avenue, near the entrance to the Holland Tunnel, which connects New York and New Jersey, and the Trinity Church parish hall.
