Some of the protesters who went there carried and distributed copies of the court order at the same time and even gave those copies to the police guarding the square, which led to "some small clashes", said Bray, who said some police beat the protesters.
The court order prohibits authorities from evacuating members of the Occupy Wall Street movement and enforcing "laws that were issued after the seizure began, or prohibiting protesters from re-entering the park with shops and other property that they used before".
